75  devices, you can define the device in your toolchain compiler preprocessor.
76 
77  - Ultra Low Power Medium-density devices are STM32L151xx and STM32L152xx
78  microcontrollers where the Flash memory density ranges between 64 and 128 Kbytes.
79  - Ultra Low Power Medium-density Plus devices are STM32L151xx, STM32L152xx and
80  STM32L162xx microcontrollers where the Flash memory density is 256 Kbytes.
81  - Ultra Low Power High-density devices are STM32L151xx, STM32L152xx and STM32L162xx
82  microcontrollers where the Flash memory density is 384 Kbytes.
83  */

286 #if defined ( __CC_ARM )
287 /* ARM Compiler
288  ------------
289  RAM functions are defined using the toolchain options.
290  Functions that are executed in RAM should reside in a separate source
291  module. Using the 'Options for File' dialog you can simply change the
292  'Code / Const' area of a module to a memory space in physical RAM.
293  Available memory areas are declared in the 'Target' tab of the
294  'Options for Target' dialog.
295 */
296  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status
297 
298 #elif defined ( __ICCARM__ )
299 /* ICCARM Compiler
300  ---------------
301  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain keyword "__ramfunc".
302 */
303  #define __RAM_FUNC __ramfunc FLASH_Status
304 
305 #elif defined ( __GNUC__ )
306 /* GNU Compiler
307  ------------
308  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain attribute
309  "__attribute__((section(".data")))".
310 */
311  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status __attribute__((section(".data")))
312 
313 #elif defined ( __TASKING__ )
314 /* TASKING Compiler
315  ----------------
316  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain pragma. This pragma is
317  defined in the stm32l1xx_flash_ramfunc.c
318 */
319  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status
320 
321 #endif

876 #define FLASH_BASE ((uint32_t)0x08000000)
877 #define SRAM_BASE ((uint32_t)0x20000000)
878 #define PERIPH_BASE ((uint32_t)0x40000000)
880 #define SRAM_BB_BASE ((uint32_t)0x22000000)
881 #define PERIPH_BB_BASE ((uint32_t)0x42000000)
883 #define FSMC_R_BASE ((uint32_t)0xA0000000)
886 #define APB1PERIPH_BASE PERIPH_BASE
887 #define APB2PERIPH_BASE (PERIPH_BASE + 0x10000)
888 #define AHBPERIPH_BASE (PERIPH_BASE + 0x20000)
889 
890 #define TIM2_BASE (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x0000)
891 #define TIM3_BASE (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x0400)
892 #define TIM4_BASE (APB1PERIPH_BASE + 0x0800)
